\f0\b\fs54 \cf0 Slow Cooked Curried Chicken with Cauliflower\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs34 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4 to 6 servings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons canola oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cloves garlic}}, minced\
{\listtext	\'95	}2-inch piece fresh ginger, minced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/3 to 1/2 cup prepared South Asian {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/curry-paste/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 curry paste}} (recommended: Patak)\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/broth/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chicken broth}}, low-sodium canned, or homemade\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups whole milk plain yogurt\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 bone-in skinless {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chicken/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chicken thighs}}, about 2 1/4 pounds\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 tablespoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 (1 pound) bag red lentils, picked over (2 1/4 cups)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 head cauliflower, broken into large florets\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 (16-ounce) cans {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chickpea/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chickpeas}}, drained and rinsed\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 bunch fresh mint or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cilantro/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cilantro}} leaves, chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 lemon, cut in wedges\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Heat the oil; add the garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant. Add the curry paste and continue to cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes more. Whisk the broth with all the aromatics in the pan; then pour the liquid into a slow cooker. Whisk the yogurt into the liquid.\
Season the chicken all over with salt and pepper. Add the chicken, lentils and remaining salt to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/slow-cooker/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 slow cooker}}. Cover and cook on HIGH for 6 hours, adding {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cauliflower/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cauliflower}} and chickpeas about half way through cooking.\
Divide curry evenly into bowls and scatter freshly torn mint or cilantro on top. Serve with a wedge of lemon.\
Cooks note: This dish can be easily adapted to make a flavorful {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vegetarian/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vegetarian}} dish. Simply cut out the chicken and use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/broth/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vegetable broth}} instead.\
